ACS, Banco BPI, Sacyr Vallehermoso : Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-04-01T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/acs-banco-bpi-sacyr-vallehermoso-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  dropped 1.5 percent to 10,576.50.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  fell 1.3 percent to 7,753.45.  Spanish stocks:  Actividades de Construccion & Servicios SA (ACS SM): The
homebuilder said it will offer its own plan for the Hochtief AG
supervisory board after the German builder it’s acquiring
proposed a list of candidates with only two ACS representatives.
ACS’s shares slipped 0.1 percent to 33.08 euros.  Natraceutical SA (NTC)  : The caffeine producer’s
chairman, Javier Adsera, asked to resign, the company said in a
filing. The shares gained 7.5 percent to 36 euro cents.  Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV)  : The construction company
said it will issue as much as 230 million euros ($326 million)
of convertible bonds with a coupon of 6.5 percent. The initial
conversion price is 10.61 euros per share. The shares fell 2
percent to 8.20 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Banco BPI SA (BPI)  : Portugal’s fifth-biggest bank didn’t
use funding from the  European Central Bank  in the first quarter,
Chief Executive Officer Fernando Ulrich said in a conference.
The stock fell 3.3 percent to 1.23 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
